# Integration Test Data Isolation Rule

When creating integration tests, always use unique namespaces and identifiers to prevent conflicts between test runs and parallel execution.

## Core Requirements

### 1. Unique Test Data
- Use unique prefixes: `Test_{timestamp}_{guid}_` or `Test_{methodName}_{guid}_`
- Include test method name in identifiers
- Never use static/hardcoded test data

### 2. Database Isolation
- Use unique database names/schemas per test run
- Implement proper cleanup between tests
- Use transaction rollback or separate test databases

### 3. File System Isolation
- Use unique directories with GUIDs
- Clean up test files after execution
- Use temp directories with unique names

## Implementation Examples

### Database Tests
```csharp
// ✅ Good
var uniqueId = $"Test_{DateTime.UtcNow:yyyyMMdd_HHmmss}_{Guid.NewGuid():N}";
var testUser = new User 
{ 
    Email = $"{uniqueId}_user@test.com",
    UserName = $"{uniqueId}_username"
};

// ❌ Bad
var testUser = new User 
{ 
    Email = "test@example.com",
    UserName = "testuser"
};
```

### File System Tests
```csharp
// ✅ Good
var testDir = Path.Combine(Path.GetTempPath(), $"Test_{Guid.NewGuid():N}");
Directory.CreateDirectory(testDir);

// ❌ Bad
var testDir = Path.Combine(Path.GetTempPath(), "TestData");
```

### API Tests
```csharp
// ✅ Good
var testId = $"test_{DateTime.UtcNow:yyyyMMdd_HHmmss}_{Guid.NewGuid():N}";
var response = await client.PostAsync("/api/resource", 
    JsonContent.Create(new { name = $"{testId}_resource" }));

// ❌ Bad
var response = await client.PostAsync("/api/resource", 
    JsonContent.Create(new { name = "test_resource" }));
```

## Test Setup Pattern
```csharp
[Test]
public async Task TestMethod_ShouldDoSomething()
{
    // Generate unique identifier for this test
    var testId = $"Test_{nameof(TestMethod_ShouldDoSomething)}_{Guid.NewGuid():N}";
    
    // Use unique data
    var testData = new TestModel { Name = $"{testId}_data" };
    
    // Test logic here...
    
    // Cleanup in finally block or test teardown
}
```

## Validation Checklist
- [ ] All test data uses unique namespaces
- [ ] Database operations are isolated
- [ ] File operations use unique paths
- [ ] Proper cleanup implemented
- [ ] Tests can run in parallel
- [ ] Tests are idempotent

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
1. Static test data (hardcoded values)
2. Shared state between tests
3. Incomplete cleanup
4. Race conditions in parallel execution
5. External dependencies without isolation

This rule ensures integration tests are robust and conflict-free across all environments.
